external_knowledge:
- "Tallest trees in the forest" refers to the highest risk score for each loan product;
- "Towers above the average risk score of the forest" means the risk score is greater than the average risk score for that loan product;
- "Loan product" is a category of loans, such as personal, car, or home loans.

- 'navigated the river of life beyond the three-decade mark' refers to age > 30;
- 'possess a risk score that doesn't raise too many eyebrows' refers to risk_score < 70;
- 'job tenure measured in years' refers to employment_duration LIKE '%years%';
- 'more than one loan application on their record' refers to HAVING COUNT(la.loan_id) > 1.

- "prominent thorn" refers to the highest fee amount for a loan;
- "more complex" refers to having more than one type of fee;
- "average thorniness" refers to the average total fees across all loans.

- 'loan_product_id' is a unique identifier for each loan product;
- 'category' refers to the type of loan product, such as personal, car, or home;
- The 'overall average loan amount' is calculated by weighting the average loan amounts by the number of applications for each product within a category.

- "Seeds of financial trust" refers to loan applications;
- "Blossomed" refers to loan applications that have been approved;
- "Strong credit garden" refers to applicants with a good credit history;
- The interest rate is a key factor in the cost of borrowing.

- A risk score above 50 indicates a lower risk of default;
- A loan amount exceeding 10,000 is considered significant;
- An income surpassing 50,000 is a threshold for financial stability.

- "garden of approved loans" refers to the set of loan applications that have been approved;
- "type of tree they belong to" refers to the loan product ID;
- "most fruitful trees" refers to the loan products with the highest total fee amounts.

- "garden of multiple loans" refers to applicants with more than one loan;
- "total interest blooms beyond 100,000" means the total interest from their loans is greater than 100,000;
- "interest harvest is more bountiful than the average" means the total interest is higher than the average total interest of all applicants with more than one loan and total interest greater than 100,000.

- 'golden seeds of prosperity' refers to loans that have been approved and have a high value (loan amount > $50,000);
- 'river of plenty' refers to an applicant's income exceeding $80,000;
- 'unblemished credit history' refers to a good credit history;
- 'mountain of gold' refers to a high loan amount;
- 'blossomed with approval' means the loan has been approved;
- 'risk level' refers to the risk category of the loan.

- "Monthly income" is calculated as the total annual income divided by 12;
- "Employment duration" is the length of time an applicant has been employed;
- "Credit score" is a numerical expression of a person's creditworthiness;
- "Loan payments" are the amounts paid by the applicant towards their loans.

- "approved loan applications" are those where the status is 'approved';
- "highest interest rates above the average" means the interest rate is greater than the average interest rate for that loan product;
- "top-ranked loan" is determined by the highest interest rate within each product.

- "Financial gardeners" refers to applicants;
- "Nurtured more than one approved loan seedling" means having more than one approved loan application;
- "Forest's average" refers to the average interest rate of all loan products.
